{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 15:06:15.496241", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive summary\n- Overall L3 network health appears normal: hosts across multiple access subnets can reach each other and the server farm with low RTT and 0% packet loss. OSPF-based reachability looks healthy.\n- A critical anomaly exists in DNS data: the A record for web0.local is misconfigured to 10.1.1.12 (an access host’s IP) instead of the web server IP in the server farm. This causes HTTP failures to web0.local from multiple subnets, although the web server is reachable and responsive by its correct IP.\n\nObserved behavior and tests\n1) Layer-3 reachability\n- Bulk reachability tests show 0% loss between multiple access hosts and the server farm devices (dns_server, web servers, load_balancer). RTTs are ~1–4 ms, typical for an emulated campus design.\n- Example: host_1_1_1_1 -> dns_server (10.200.0.2) ping: 0% loss, avg ~4.08 ms.\n\n2) DNS resolution and service access\n- Clients use the DNS at 10.200.0.2 (checked /etc/resolv.conf on hosts).\n- Name resolution results from hosts:\n  - web99.local resolves to 10.200.0.7 (load_balancer). Access tests are successful and stable from both hosts.\n  - web1.local resolves to 10.200.0.4. HTTP access is successful (TTFB ~0.26–1.36s, total ~1.06–2.17s).\n  - web0.local resolves to 10.1.1.12 on both hosts (getent/dig confirm). HTTP access fails instantly or returns only name lookup timing (connect/starttransfer 0.000), consistent with connecting to a non-web host or connection refused.\n- Direct IP test of web_server_0 (10.200.0.3) is successful from both hosts:\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> http://10.200.0.3: starttransfer ~1.12–1.40s; total ~1.92–2.21s.\n  - host_2_1_1_1 -> http://10.200.0.3: total ranges ~1.02–2.12s.\n  This confirms the web server is up and reachable over the network.\n\n3) DNS server inspection (dns_server)\n- BIND listening on 10.200.0.2:53 and localhost; service is running (named).\n- Zone file /etc/bind/db.local is authoritative for the local zone:\n  - ns1.local A 10.200.0.2\n  - web0.local A 10.1.1.12  <-- anomalous\n  - web1.local A 10.200.0.4\n  - web2.local A 10.200.0.5\n  - web3.local A 10.200.0.6\n  - web99.local A 10.200.0.7\n- The configured web server inventory shows web_server_0 at 10.200.0.3; therefore web0.local should map into 10.200.0.3 within 10.200.0.0/24, not an access host IP (10.1.1.12).\n\nAnomalies detected\n- Incorrect DNS A record for web0.local pointing to 10.1.1.12 (an access host IP). This is inconsistent with:\n  - The server inventory (web_server_0 is 10.200.0.3).\n  - The behavior of web1–web3, which correctly map into the 10.200.0.0/24 server farm.\n- Impact: Any client attempting to access http://web0.local will resolve to 10.1.1.12 and fail (or inadvertently connect to a user host if a service is running there). Verified from multiple subnets. This is a service availability and potential security exposure issue.\n\nFault localization\n- Faulty device: dns_server (BIND).\n- Faulty component: Authoritative zone data for “local” in /etc/bind/db.local.\n- The issue is not in routing, switching, host DNS configuration, or the web_server_0 host itself (reachable and responsive by IP).\n\nRoot cause\n- Misconfiguration of the DNS zone: web0.local A record set to 10.1.1.12 instead of the server farm address for web_server_0 (expected 10.200.0.3 according to the provided inventory/topology). This causes name-based access to web0.local to fail despite normal network and server operation.\n\nAdditional notes\n- OSPF/IGP appears stable based on end-to-end reachability; no evidence of routing blackholes or asymmetry.\n- DNS recursion is disabled (recursion no) on dns_server; this is acceptable for an authoritative-only local zone and not implicated in this issue.\n- Backend web servers behind the load balancer are not exposed in DNS and were not directly accessible during tests, consistent with the design goal.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 14471, "output_tokens": 3840, "total_tokens": 18311, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 13952}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2752}}}
